==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sneak current
<hw>Sneak current</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A current which, though
too feeble to blow the usual fuse or to injure at once telegraph or
telephone instruments, will in time burn them out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sneaker</ent>⟦br⟧
